    \td{These are not \em{decisions} made w/r/t criteria. The notion of criteria and choice aren't suited for talking about transitions \em{between} vocabularies. }
    \td{These are decisions based on objective criteria (e.g. better 'cutting the world at the joints') }
    \td{These are decisions based on subjective criteria (arbitrary choices).}
  }
